  <flowering_time>fall</flowering_time>
  <flowering_time>oct</flowering_time>
  <flowering_time>nov</flowering_time>
  <flowering_time>dec</flowering_time>
  <flowering_time>winter</flowering_time>
  <habitat>on shelving rocks</habitat>
  <habitat>road banks in chaparral or coastal sage</habitat>
  <elevation>0–200 m;</elevation>
  <us_distribution>Calif.</us_distribution>
  <discussion>Variety saxatilis frequently grows in coastal areas of Santa Barbara County on steep bluffs overlooking the ocean, and at lower elevations near beaches, and in canyon mouths along the lower south slopes of the Santa Ynez Mountains.</discussion>
</treatment>

